<br>
TLC is simply heaven for the higher end game. But my number one reason why I love FV is the people. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kendrikfv>kendrik fv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 5:47:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /nod</span><hr size=1> Couldn't agree with you more, Auno. <br>
/cheer the people on FV<br>
<br>
Why do you say TLC is great for the end game? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 5:57:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> agreed</span><hr size=1> TLC is good because it creates a challenge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 6:24:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: agreed</span><hr size=1> Bah, I can create my own challenge if I want it. I'd rather not have code forcing me into it just because OTHER people are lazy... but that's another topic that's been beaten to death.<br>
<br>
I like FV 'cause I can RP and no one will look at me funny. I really wish I could have more than one character, though, because I have a lot of different character concepts I'ld like to play with, and this is the only server where I'll actually get people playing back with me on a regular basis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhueth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hueth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 6:30:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> The people really do make this server, I agree.  <br>
<br>
<br>
As far as TLC goes, well, I know this may be an unpopular view, but if everyone has the best  items and epics weapons...then doesn't that turn them into just....standard items and normal weapons?<br>
<br>
I will likely never have my epic.  I will not have the best items.  I am not motivated to go get better &quot;stuff.&quot;  I will most likely be wearing my Sr. Apprentice robe at level 29+.<br>
<br>
I'm OK  with not having stuff.  Anyway, people will look better with their TLC-required quest stuff standing next to me with my normal stuff.<br>
<br>
The &quot;haves&quot; need their &quot;have nots&quot;... otherwise the whole system breaks down!  <br>
<br>
