<br>
You shouldn't be so down on yourself. In fact, I recomment the Compendium on my site, in particular the last section. One of the reasons that I wrote the Compendium was for people that thought they couldn't Role Play or they weren't just good enough. I wrote it to help all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>Sovereign Lord of the <a href=http://www.1stfistoflight.com>1st Fist of Light</a><br>Firiona Vie</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 8:05:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> I agree with everything you've put there. You didn't add removal of the NO DROP flag on all but a few items. I love this. Finally I have a shot at doing quests without enduring horrible camps.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 10:55:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Actually ..</span><hr size=1> .. it's not TLC that's great, it's the no no-drops that TLC gives us.  There are so many things you can do there that it almost pays for all the ugly TLC questing issues.<br>
<br>
Other than the no-drop removal, I can honestly say that I don't like any of the rules.  Maybe languages a bit, but it should have been done by making NPC's only converse in their native tongues and merchants/questers only dealing with you if they can talk with you rather than keeping PCs from talking to each other.  Inhibiting people from interacting == bad.<br>
<br>
My guess is that more people leave this server from not being able to talk to anyone but their own race than for any other reason. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 11:21:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Actually ..</span><hr size=1> Actually...the languages is one of the things i love...why would i need to learn another language if everyone spoke common?...i am a warrior and would have no need to learn another then...into everything that encourages RP)<br>
<br>
Dhugal Forgefyre <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 11:33:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You would need to ..</span><hr size=1> .. learn another language to interact with NCPs; ie. to bank, buy/sell, and quest in another town.  That's how I would have done it.  The incentive should be based on things to do in the game rather than a basic requirement so people can talk with each other.  Same result of making languages necessary, different reason for the necessity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 1:27:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You would need to ..</span><hr size=1> OMG, thats a great idea. Make the npc's in NEriak only speak DE etc. That would provide a strong incentive to learn languages and possibly create a market for low level players to &quot;teach&quot; languages to higher level players doing quests.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
Giver of "da juice" (tm)
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=celle>Celle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 1:45:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You would need to ..</span><hr size=1> I totally agree! I thought it was really lame that orcs still taunt you in Common, and you have no trouble communicating with any other npc in Norrath. Although I don't think it's something that would be simple to implement in the current game, for balance reasons. It would cut you off from a lot of quests that and some races would have the edge over others. Maybe EQ2? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=celle>Celle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 2:00:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> I have a love/hate relationship with the 1 character limit. I love it because it prevents most twinking, which keeps the l4m3rs away for the most part. I hate it because I love Firiona Vie and couldn't possibly play on any other server (well, I haven't tried PVP) and I've deleted two characters (both level 9, so no big loss) to try other races / classes / roleplaying concepts.<br>
<br>
I just started EQ a couple of weeks ago. I consider myself lucky; the game seems fresh and new to me. I hear others on the boards and also a friend of mine speak of being burnt-out. Dyshira (My love!) and I started playing the same time I did. We both have accounts, which we share. After playing on Firiona Vie for a while, I realized I couldn't stand not playing at least one other character, so I bought another copy (Trilogy + Luclin and monthlyfee, ouch). <br>
<br>
And please don't flame me, I play the characters entirely seperately, I am adamantly against twinking, at least for myself. I don't want to spoil the fun for myself or others. How everyone else plays is up to them, but I don't prefer twinking at all.<br>
<br>
I have two characters because I want to be able to roleplay two entriely different characters. It's hard to say what I like about Firiona Vie more, the role-playing or the lack of twinked characters better I guess both are what attract good players to the server, so either way.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=charlemaine>Charlemaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 8:25:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I like FV 'cause I can RP and no one will look at me funny. I really wish I could have more than one character, though, because I have a lot of different character concepts I'ld like to play with, and this is the only server where I'll actually get people playing back with me on a regular basis.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I agree wholeheartedly. I like to make several characters on a server I'm planning to join - run them up to about 10th level each, that way I can get a feel of the population. Can't do that here. <br>
<br>
But in a way that's good. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubormwarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borm Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 10:14:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> The single character is the best thing about our server for me. We have a small population and when that is combined with a single character per account you have the best possible personal accountability in the game. <br>
<br>
In FV you are only as good as your reputation. Couple that with the language barriers and you have some great fun. When Borm as a level 12 in the Warrens he did something to offend some elf. I had no idea what it could have been, it was obviously not intentional, nonetheless, given the language barriers we could not communicate to try and smooth things out.<br>
<br>
At first that upset me, I needed to try and fix it. Then it struck me that this way was much more complex. I would either have to be creative and try to fix things or live with the knowledge that I might never be able to fix it. This server forces us to do new and different things, to grow as an EQ player. <br>
<br>
Borm, still most likely a goat in some poor elf's eyes! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 10:30:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> I love the single character limit, I love the way it stops twinking BUT I do have 1 dislike.<br>
<br>
I hate the way friends decide that they would like to try X and delete their 40+ characters to start all over again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is something I find depressing. Me, well I will never delete any character I have ever made anywhere. Hell I even have issues with deleteing mules. I see so many people re starting this has 2 effects.<br>
<br>
1. Guarentees a continued low lvl population (which is not a bad thing, I have also noticed there are quite a few newbies both from other servers and TRULY new :-)<br>
<br>
2. It depletes folks from the higher level ranges. I hope enough people hang on or buy second accounts so there is a viable bigger population.<br>
<br>
That said I love the low pop :-) love going to dungeons and there being only the team I have brought with me. Love languages, love TLC (though it has bitten me a couple of times).<br>
<br>
With TLC I find there are many younger folks who if you get to know them are more than welcome to do quests for you even if they are not guilded with you. And if you are guilded, even easier :-)<br>
<br>
I love FV.<br>
<br>
Its my last best chance for EQ :-)<br>
<br>
